comments.body: This still needs to be audited for the `staging` and `prod` environments

While this is unrelated to the resolution of this issue, the following error was logged for the `prod` environment when restarting the `dspace` systemd service:

```
2020-08-25 08:38:35,369 ERROR org.dspace.statistics.SolrLogger @ The GeoLite Database file is missing (/dspace/config/GeoLiteCity.dat)! Solr Statistics cannot generate location based rep
orts! Please see the DSpace installation instructions for instructions to install this file.
java.io.FileNotFoundException: /dspace/config/GeoLiteCity.dat (No such file or directory)
```

There is a discrepancy between environments, as https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01jh343w268 has different authorization policies at the Item-level from https://dataspace-staging.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01jh343w268

Items with the `pu.mudd.walkin` metadata values should also have the authorization `SrTheses_Bitstream_Read_Mudd` set for the Bitstreams, otherwise anonymous users just on the VPN will be able to download the PDFs.

pomegranate.title: Exhibit home for eastasian very slow to load

comments.body: The exhibit has 6676 custom fields called `override-title_ssim`. Looks like #731.

I deleted the duplicates of that field for now. I didn't do anything to any other exhibits. Here are the duplicate counts:

```
Spotlight::CustomField.all.select{|v| v.slug.length > 30}.map(&:exhibit_id).group_by{|i| i}.map{|k,v| [Spotlight::Exhibit.find(k).slug, v.count]}
=> [["cotsen", 615], ["hellenica", 194], ["music", 494], ["eastasian", 97], ["lapidus", 315], ["pudl0135", 256], ["scheide", 206], ["neareast", 92], ["pudl0058", 38], ["papyri", 337], ["Fragments", 9], ["ealtoc", 1]]
```

We noticed it was true for Alternative in one collection too, but it's definitely a huge issue for Override Title. We're likely doing something wrong for that field, since we create it ourselves at index time.

We think https://github.com/pulibrary/pomegranate/blob/master/spec/models/iiif_resource_spec.rb#L134-L149 tests the fact that new custom fields aren't created on every index. It must be creating override title custom fields elsewhere? We've also noticed some exhibits have multiple override title custom fields.

There is a valid custom field with a slug longer than 30 characters. When cleaning up do this:

```ruby
Spotlight::CustomField.all.select{|v| v.slug.length > 30}.select{|x| x.slug.match(/\d/)}.each do |x|
  x.destroy
end
```

[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/builds/32971982/badge)](https://coveralls.io/builds/32971982)

Coverage remained the same at 100.0% when pulling **2b669625027890ad6fa7188acb87e76b75aa97be on 876-update-gbl** into **fcb28331f0edd9781477f0b5c16a927e0f97ecf9 on master**.
